Halve @ciabatta bread{2%unit} and toast until golden brown in a #toaster{}.

Place @pulled pork{8%ounce} in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}; using two
#forks{}, shred into smaller pieces. Stir in @ketchup{1%unit} and half the
@fry seasoning{1/2%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings). Cover with #plastic wrap{}
and microwave until heated through and flavors have melded, ~{2-3%minutes}.

In a small #bowl{}, combine @dijon mustard{2%teaspoon} and @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}
and mix thoroughly.

Place toasted ciabattas on a clean work surface. Spread bottom halves of
ciabattas with Dijonnaise. Top with @swiss cheese{2%slice}, pulled pork,
and as much @sliced dill pickle{1%unit} as you like. Close sandwiches.

Halve sandwiches on a diagonal and serve with any remaining pickle on the side.

> Pulled Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.